Power of 4
Given an integer n, return true if it is a power of four. Otherwise, return false.

An integer n is a power of four, if there exists an integer x such that n == 4x.


CODE:
class Solution {
    public boolean isPowerOfFour(int n) {
        if(n<=0)
        {
            return false;
        }
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
        {
            if(Math.pow(4,i)==n)
            {
            return true;
            }
            if(Math.pow(4,i)>n)
            {
                break;
            }

        }
                return false;

    }
}
